# CursorCraft project rules

CursorCraft is a local-first, static marketing + tools site that teaches teams how to
use Cursor securely and cost-effectively. The site must itself model those principles.

## Architecture & stack
- Astro with `output: 'static'`. Ship static HTML by default.
- React (`@astrojs/react`) is for interactive **islands only** (e.g. the Config Analyzer).
  Do not reach for React/hydration when a static `.astro` component will do.
- TypeScript in **strict** mode. No `any` without justification; prefer precise types.
- Tailwind CSS (v4, via `@tailwindcss/vite`) for styling. Use the design tokens defined
  in `src/styles/global.css` (ink/paper/accent scales) rather than ad-hoc hex values.
- Content lives in MDX content collections under `src/content/guides`.

## Security conventions (non-negotiable)
- NEVER add backend calls, telemetry, or analytics that transmit user-provided file
  contents, keys, or secrets.
- The Config Analyzer and any tool must run **100% client-side**. No network calls with
  user data. No `localStorage`/`sessionStorage` for user file contents, keys, or secrets —
  in-memory React state only.
- Never commit secrets. Respect `.cursorignore`.

## Quality bar
- Accessibility: WCAG AA. Semantic landmarks, keyboard nav, visible focus rings,
  `prefers-reduced-motion` support, descriptive alt text and aria labels.
- SEO: every page goes through `BaseLayout` with a unique title, description, canonical,
  OG image, and appropriate JSON-LD. One `<h1>` per page; correct heading order.
- Performance: minimal JS, preload fonts, no layout shift, lazy-load below-fold media.
- Write real, senior-level content. No lorem ipsum, no invented Cursor feature specifics —
  phrase uncertain behavior generally.

## Conventions
- Reusable UI components live in `src/components/ui`.
- Keep diffs small and reviewable. Prefer composition over duplication.
- Use the `Callout` component for security warnings and cost tips.
